  "body": "The [GraphQL spec](https://graphql.github.io/graphql-spec/June2018/#sec-Errors) says \r\n> If an error can be associated to a particular point in the requested GraphQL document, it should contain an entry with the key locations with a list of locations, where each location is a map with the keys line and column, both positive numbers starting from 1 which describe the beginning of an associated syntax element.\r\n\r\nAnd it says the same about the path to that field.\r\n\r\nI run this query\r\n```graphql\r\n{\r\n  block(hash: 99) {\r\n    hash\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is what Geth returns now\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"errors\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"message\": \"Unexpected type for Bytes32: 99\"\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"data\": {}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is what I expect it to return\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"errors\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"message\": \"Unexpected type for Bytes32: 99\",\r\n      \"locations\": [ { \"line\": 2, \"column\": 15 } ],\r\n      \"path\": [ \"block\", \"hash\" ]\r\n    }\r\n  ]}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.0-stable`\r\nOS & Version: OSX\r\n",
